---
title: "onReport (WorkflowRouter)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_check_access: require whenNotPaused, FORWARDER_ROLE
    q_check_access --> q_extract_workflow: access granted
    q_extract_workflow --> q_check_zero_wf: workflowId = bytes32(metadata[:32])
    q_check_zero_wf --> q_revert_zero: workflowId == bytes32(0)
    q_revert_zero --> [*]: revert InvalidZeroValue
    q_check_zero_wf --> q_check_allowlisted: workflowId != bytes32(0)
    q_check_allowlisted --> q_revert_not_allowed: NOT s_allowlistedWorkflowIds.contains(workflowId)
    q_revert_not_allowed --> [*]: revert WorkflowIdNotAllowlisted
    q_check_allowlisted --> q_decode_report: workflow is allowlisted
    q_decode_report --> q_extract_selector: (target, data) = decode(report)
    q_extract_selector --> q_check_selector: selector = first 4 bytes of data
    q_check_selector --> q_check_target: selector NOT allowlisted for target
    q_check_target --> q_revert_target: target NOT allowlisted
    q_revert_target --> [*]: revert TargetNotAllowlisted
    q_check_target --> q_revert_selector: target allowlisted but selector not
    q_revert_selector --> [*]: revert SelectorNotAllowlisted
    q_check_selector --> q_call: selector allowlisted
    q_call --> [*]: _call(target, data)

    note right of q_check_selector
        INV-001: Three-level access control: workflowId -> target -> selector
        INV-002: Router does not hold funds, only routes calls
        INV-003: Only FORWARDER_ROLE can submit reports (trusted automation)
    end note
